<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVING REGARD TO THE TREATY ESTABLISHING THE EUROPEAN ECONOMIC COMMUNITY, AN IN PARTICULAR ARTICLE 100 </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit </eesti>
<inglise> THEREOF; </inglise>
<eesti> 100, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVING REGARD TO THE PROPOSAL FROM THE COMMISSION; HAVING REGARD TO THE OPINION OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT (1); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> HAVING REGARD TO THE OPINION OF THE ECONOMIC AND SOCIAL COMMITTEE (2); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PRINCIPLE THAT MEN AND WOMEN SHOULD RECEIVE EQUAL PAY CONTAINED IN ARTICLE </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> 119 OF THE TREATY IS AN INTEGRAL PART OF THE ESTABLISHMENT AND FUNCTIONING OF THE COMMON MARKET; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS IT IS PRIMARILY THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE MEMBER STATES TO ENSURE THE APPLICATION OF THIS PRINCIPLE BY MEANS OF APPROPRIATE LAWS, REGULATIONS AND ADMINISTRATIVE PROVISIONS; </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepingu artiklis 119 s&auml;testatud meeste ja naiste v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte rakendamine on &uuml;histuru rajamise ja toimimise lahutamatu osa; </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS THE COUNCIL RESOLUTION OF 21 JANUARY 1974 (3) CONCERNING A SOCIAL ACTION PROGRAMME, AIMED AT MAKING IT POSSIBLE TO HARMONIZE LIVING AND WORKING CONDITIONS WHILE THE IMPROVEMENT IS BEING MAINTAINED AND AT </inglise>
<eesti> eelk&otilde;ige on liikmesriikide kohustus tagada selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tte rakendamine asjakohaste &otilde;igus- ja haldusnormidega; </eesti>
<inglise> ACHIEVING A BALANCED SOCIAL AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT OF THE COMMUNITY, RECOGNIZED THAT PRIORITY SHOULD BE GIVEN TO ACTION TAKEN ON BEHALF OF WOMEN AS REGARDS ACCESS TO EMPLOYMENT AND VOCATIONAL TRAINING AND </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 21. jaanuari 1974. aasta sotsiaalprogrammi k&auml;sitlevas resolutsioonis, mille eesm&auml;rk on &uuml;htlustada elu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi, neid samal ajal parandades, ning saavutada &uuml;henduse tasakaalustatud sotsiaalne ja majanduslik areng, t&otilde;deti, et esmaj&auml;rjekorras tuleks v&otilde;tta meetmeid naiste olukorra parandamiseks seoses t&ouml;&ouml; saamise, kutse&otilde;ppe ja edutamisega ning t&ouml;&ouml;tingimustega, kaasa arvatud t&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine; </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS IT IS DESIRABLE TO REINFORCE THE BASIC LAWS BY STANDARDS AIMED AT FACILITATING THE PRATICAL APPLICATION OF THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUALITY IN SUCH A WAY THAT ALL EMPLOYEES IN THE COMMUNITY CAN BE PROTECTED IN THESE </inglise>
<eesti> soovitav on p&otilde;hilisi seadusi t&auml;iendada standarditega, mis h&otilde;lbustaksid v&otilde;rdsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaldamist sellisel viisil, et oleks v&otilde;imalik kaitsta k&otilde;iki &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid; </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS DIFFERENCES CONTINUE TO EXIST IN THE VARIOUS MEMBER STATES DESPITE THE EFFORTS MADE TO APPLY THE RESOLUTION OF THE CONFERENCE OF THE MEMBER STATES OF 30 DECEMBER 1961 ON EQUAL PAY FOR MEN AND WOMEN AND </inglise>
<eesti> eri liikmesriikide vahel p&uuml;sivad erinevused, hoolimata j&otilde;upingutustest meeste ja naiste v&otilde;rdse tasustamisega seotud otsuste rakendamiseks, mis liikmesriikide konverentsil 30. detsembril 1961 vastu v&otilde;eti - sellep&auml;rast tuleb v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaldamisega seotud siseriiklikud &otilde;igusaktid &uuml;htlustada, </eesti>
<inglise> WHEREAS, THEREFORE, THE NATIONAL PROVISIONS SHOULD BE APPROXIMATED AS REGARDS APPLICATION OF THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUAL PAY, </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI: </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL INTRODUCE INTO THEIR NATIONAL LEGAL SYSTEMS SUCH MEASURES AS ARE NECESSARY TO ENABLE ALL EMPLOYEES WHO CONSIDER THEMSELVES WRONGED BY FAILURE TO APPLY THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUAL PAY TO PURSUE THEIR </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad oma siseriiklikes &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemides meetmed, mis v&otilde;imaldaksid isikutel, kes arvavad, et neid on v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte eiramise t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igusvastaselt koheldud, n&otilde;uda oma &otilde;iguste kaitset kohtu kaudu, olles vastava v&otilde;imaluse korral esmalt p&ouml;&ouml;rdunud p&auml;devate asutuste poole. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL ABOLISH ALL DISCRIMINATION BETWEEN MEN AND WOMEN ARISING FROM LAWS, REGULATIONS OR ADMINISTRATIVE PROVISIONS WHICH IS CONTRARY TO THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUAL PAY. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kaotavad t&auml;ielikult soolise diskrimineerimise, mida p&otilde;hjustavad v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttega vastuolus olevad &otilde;igus- v&otilde;i haldusnormid. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 4 MEMBER STATES SHALL TAKE THE NECESSARY MEASURES TO ENSURE THAT PROVISIONS APPEARING IN COLLECTIVE </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> AGREEMENTS, WAGE SCALES, WAGE AGREEMENTS OR INDIVIDUAL CONTRACTS OF EMPLOYMENT WHICH ARE CONTRARY TO THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUAL PAY SHALL BE, OR MAY BE DECLARED, NULL AND VOID OR MAY BE AMENDED. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et kollektiivlepingute s&auml;tted, palgaastmestikud, palgakokkulepped ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingud, mis on vastuolus v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttega, on t&uuml;hised v&otilde;i tunnistatakse kehtetuks v&otilde;i muudetakse. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL TAKE THE NECESSARY MEASURES TO PROTECT EMPLOYEES AGAINST DISMISSAL BY THE EMPLOYER AS A REACTION TO A COMPLAINT WITHIN THE UNDERTAKING OR TO ANY LEGAL PROCEEDINGS AIMED AT ENFORCING COMPLIANCE </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vajalikud meetmed, et kaitsta t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid vallandamise eest, kui see on t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutegevus ettev&otilde;ttesisesele kaebusele v&otilde;i kohtumenetlusele, mille eesm&auml;rk on tagada v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgimine. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL, IN ACCORDANCE WITH THEIR NATIONAL CIRCUMSTANCES AND LEGAL SYSTEMS, TAKE THE MEASURES </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vajalikud meetmed koosk&otilde;las siseriiklike olude ning &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemiga, et tagada v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise> NECESSARY TO ENSURE THAT THE PRINCIPLE OF EQUAL PAY IS APPLIED. THEY SHALL SEE THAT EFFECTIVE MEANS ARE </inglise>
<eesti> Nad j&auml;lgivad, et selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tte t&auml;itmise tagamiseks on olemas t&otilde;husad vahendid. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL TAKE CARE THAT THE PROVISIONS ADOPTED PURSUANT TO THIS DIRECTIVE, TOGETHER WITH THE RELEVANT PROVISIONS ALREADY IN FORCE, ARE BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF EMPLOYEES BY ALL APPROPRIATE MEANS, </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kannavad hoolt selle eest, k&auml;esoleva direktiivi alusel vastuv&otilde;etud s&auml;tted ja juba kehtivad asjakohased s&auml;tted tehakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele sobival viisil teatavaks, n&auml;iteks nende t&ouml;&ouml;kohas. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> MEMBER STATES SHALL COMMUNICATE TO THE COMMISSION THE TEXTS OF THE LAWS, REGULATIONS AND ADMINISTRATIVE PROVISIONS WHICH THEY ADOPT IN THE FIELD COVERED BY THIS DIRECTIVE. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas nende poolt vastu v&otilde;etud &otilde;igus- ja haldusnormide tekstid. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> WITHIN TWO YEARS OF THE EXPIRY OF THE ONE-YEAR PERIOD REFERRED TO IN ARTICLE 8, MEMBER STATES SHALL FORWARD ALL NECESSARY INFORMATION TO THE COMMISSION TO ENABLE IT TO DRAW UP A REPORT ON THE APPLICATION OF THIS DIRECTIVE </inglise>
<eesti> Kahe aasta jooksul p&auml;rast artiklis 8 viidatud aastase t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist esitavad liikmesriigid komisjonile kogu vajaliku teabe, v&otilde;imaldamaks komisjonil koostada n&otilde;ukogule aruanne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> ARTICLE 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> THIS DIRECTIVE IS ADDRESSED TO THE MEMBER STATES. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
